seems string.Replace actually breaks when trying to use it recursively, sometimes it just breaks when using normally, i made my own so i'll put it here for people```c
    string RecursiveStringReplace( string str, string find, string replace )
    {
        int idxFind;
        string beforeFind, afterFind;

        while ( true )
        {
            idxFind = str.IndexOf( find );
            if ( idxFind == -1 )    break;

            beforeFind = str.Substring( 0, idxFind );
            afterFind = str.Substring( idxFind + find.Length(), str.Length() - idxFind - find.Length() );
            str = beforeFind + replace + afterFind;
        }

        return str;
    }```

